{
  "stem": "7069.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was an old, old-- what's the word-- German word is Festung-- a old citadel, so to speak, with, with catacombs underneath it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Around it was surrounded by a big moat with, with a a drawbridge like the old medieval times.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, it was a wall all around it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And people were very much confined in that  little place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "People would, in a small room maybe, a room by 15 by 15, there would sometimes be 20 people would be put in there like sardines laid out for the night on the floor on some sacks, one next to the other.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I want to, to be sure that this picture of the artistry does not mislead anybody.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the most fiendish thing, a two-sided-- like a coin with two sides, a two-sided, two-sided thing, two-sided thing that was ever developed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Theresienstadt, we-- allow me to interject here, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because part of the fiendish thing is also that Hitler allowed a couple of delegations to come.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Once was the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And another one was the King of Denmark.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Had about 500 Jews in there, and he was pestering Hitler so much that finally he allowed-- that Hitler finally allowed-- or Himmler, whoever would be at that time the commander of the-- finally allowed to have a, a Danish delegation come to that camp.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And just-- this is an important scene.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I think I have to point that out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was called out during the night to help setting up this thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was the big marketplace.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were sent to the warehouse.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was listed apparently as a handy fellow.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
